---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getTranslations, getLocalePath } from '../../i18n/translations';

const lang = 'en-us';
const t = getTranslations(lang);
---

<BaseLayout
  title={t.meta.itineraries_title}
  description={t.meta.itineraries_description}
  lang={lang}
  pageKey="itineraries"
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative bg-charcoal text-white py-20 overflow-hidden">
    <img src="/images/itinerari-hero.jpg" alt="Amalfi Coast itineraries" class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover opacity-20" loading="eager" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"/>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-charcoal/80"></div>
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <p class="text-white/80 text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-3">Plan your trip</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold font-serif mb-4">Amalfi Coast Itineraries</h1>
      <p class="text-white/80 text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">1 day, 3 days or 1 week: detailed itineraries to make the most of the Amalfi Coast however much time you have.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
      The Amalfi Coast can be visited in one (intense) day or savoured for weeks. The difference is enormous: someone with just one day will see the iconic sights but rarely what lies beyond the postcard; someone with a week can discover the quieter villages, hike the trails, eat at local restaurants, and stop to watch the sunset. These itineraries have been designed to optimise every hour, whatever time you have available.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- 1 day -->
  <section class="pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

      <div class="bg-white rounded-[2rem] shadow-sm border border-slate-100 overflow-hidden mb-12">
        <div class="bg-med-blue text-white p-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
            <span class="bg-white/20 text-white text-sm font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-full">1 day</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-serif">The best of the coast in one day</h2>
          <p class="text-white/80 mt-2">For those arriving from Naples or Salerno for the day. Intense but unforgettable.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-8">
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 text-center">
                <span class="text-med-blue font-bold text-sm">08:00</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Arrive in Amalfi by ferry</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">Take the morning ferry from Naples or Salerno. Arriving in Amalfi by sea is one of the most exciting moments of the trip. Drop your bags and explore the Cathedral square.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 text-center">
                <span class="text-med-blue font-bold text-sm">09:30</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Sant'Andrea Cathedral & Valle dei Mulini</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">Visit the magnificent Cathedral (free access to the square, paid museum). Then walk the Valle dei Mulini to see the ancient paper mills. 1h30 in total.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 text-center">
                <span class="text-med-blue font-bold text-sm">11:30</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Ferry to Positano</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">25 minutes of ferry with spectacular views. In Positano, climb to the Church of Santa Maria Assunta and enjoy the panorama over the coloured rooftops.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 text-center">
                <span class="text-med-blue font-bold text-sm">13:30</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Lunch in Positano</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">Find a trattoria on the Via dei Mulini or along the promenade. Spaghetti alle vongole or linguine al limone are essential.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 text-center">
                <span class="text-med-blue font-bold text-sm">15:00</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Spiaggia Grande</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">2 hours on the beach in Positano. The water is beautiful even in the afternoon. Hire a sun lounger and umbrella at a beach club.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 text-center">
                <span class="text-med-blue font-bold text-sm">18:00</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Aperitivo and sunset</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">Positano has some of the finest terrace bars in Italy. A Campari Spritz watching the sun sink into the sea is worth the trip alone.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 text-center">
                <span class="text-med-blue font-bold text-sm">19:30</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Return by bus or ferry</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">SITA bus to Sorrento (then Circumvesuviana to Naples) or evening ferry to Salerno or Naples, depending on your destination.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- 3 days -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-[2rem] shadow-sm border border-slate-100 overflow-hidden mb-12">
        <div class="bg-teal-700 text-white p-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
            <span class="bg-white/20 text-white text-sm font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-full">3 days</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-serif">Three days on the coast</h2>
          <p class="text-teal-100 mt-2">Ideal base: Amalfi or Praiano. Perfect balance between iconic sights and discoveries.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-8">
          <div class="space-y-8">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-lg mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-7 h-7 bg-teal-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-teal-700 text-sm font-bold">1</span>
                Day 1 - Amalfi and surroundings
              </h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-teal-500 font-bold">Morning:</span> Arrival and check-in. Visit Sant'Andrea Cathedral, Piazza del Duomo, Valle dei Mulini.</li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-teal-500 font-bold">Lunch:</span> Trattoria in the old town. Scialatielli ai frutti di mare.</li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-teal-500 font-bold">Afternoon:</span> Ferry to the Grotta dello Smeraldo at Conca dei Marini (45-minute round trip).</li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-teal-500 font-bold">Evening:</span> Dinner in Amalfi with artisan limoncello.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-lg mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-7 h-7 bg-teal-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-teal-700 text-sm font-bold">2</span>
                Day 2 - Positano and Praiano
              </h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-teal-500 font-bold">Morning:</span> Ferry to Positano. Visit Santa Maria Assunta Church, Via dei Mulini, shops.</li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-teal-500 font-bold">Lunch:</span> In Positano - even standing with a focaccia.</li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-teal-500 font-bold">Afternoon:</span> Bus to Praiano (15 minutes). Head down to Marina di Praia and swim in the turquoise cove.</li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-teal-500 font-bold">Evening:</span> Aperitivo in Praiano watching the sunset towards Positano.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-lg mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-7 h-7 bg-teal-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-teal-700 text-sm font-bold">3</span>
                Day 3 - Ravello and Cetara
              </h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-teal-500 font-bold">Morning:</span> Bus from Amalfi to Ravello (30 minutes). Villa Rufolo, belvedere terrace, old town.</li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-teal-500 font-bold">Lunch:</span> In Ravello, at a restaurant with a sea-view terrace.</li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-teal-500 font-bold">Afternoon:</span> Return to Amalfi and bus to Cetara (20 minutes). Visit the fishing village, taste the anchovy colatura.</li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-teal-500 font-bold">Evening:</span> Dinner in Cetara (prices much lower than Positano). Depart the next day.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- 1 week -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-[2rem] shadow-sm border border-slate-100 overflow-hidden">
        <div class="bg-amalfi-terracotta text-white p-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
            <span class="bg-white/20 text-white text-sm font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-full">1 week</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-serif">One week on the coast</h2>
          <p class="text-orange-100 mt-2">For those who want to go beyond the postcard. Hikes, hidden villages, local life.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-8">
          <div class="space-y-4 text-sm text-slate-600">
            <div class="bg-orange-50 rounded-2xl p-5">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Days 1–3</h3>
              <p>Follow the 3-day itinerary above. Take your time to explore the iconic sights without rushing.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-orange-50 rounded-2xl p-5">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Day 4 - Path of the Gods</h3>
              <p>The coast's most famous trek: from Bomerano (Agerola) to Nocelle above Positano. 7.8 km with unforgettable views. Moderate level, 3–4 hours.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-orange-50 rounded-2xl p-5">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Day 5 - Vietri and Salerno</h3>
              <p>Visit the ceramics workshops in Vietri sul Mare (one hour), then continue to Salerno: the seafront, the medieval old town, and the Diocesan Museum are excellent and little-known.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-orange-50 rounded-2xl p-5">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Day 6 - Boat trip</h3>
              <p>Rent a boat (with or without skipper) from Amalfi or Positano and explore the sea caves, stacks and coves inaccessible by land. One of the finest experiences on the coast.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-orange-50 rounded-2xl p-5">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Day 7 - Slow day</h3>
              <p>Choose your favourite beach, a good book, a restaurant for lunch and no programme. The coast is wonderful this way too.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-med-blue py-16 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">How do I get to the coast?</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">All the options: train, ferry, bus and private transfers.</p>
      <a href={getLocalePath(lang, 'getting-here')}
        class="inline-block bg-med-blue text-white font-semibold px-8 py-3 rounded-full hover:bg-med-blue transition-colors">
        Transport guide
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
